# ============================================================
# HFTowns — AUTO-GENERATED by HFTownExtractor
# Map: GM_Eden
# 
# This file was AUTO-CREATED on first boot of this map. The
# extractor walked the loaded world for every entity carrying a
# MapDescriptorComponent (named locations) and wrote each as a
# town entry below. The wasteland spawn system is now active
# on this map without any further admin action.
# 
# WHAT TO DO WITH THIS FILE:
#  1. (Optional) Review the entries below.
#  2. (Optional) Edit the radius / type / name as you see fit.
#  3. (Optional) Delete entries you don't want as towns.
#  4. (Optional) Add entries the extractor missed (use HFCoordTool).
#  5. Restart the server when changes are made.
# 
# To re-run the extractor (overwrites this file with fresh data):
# delete this file and restart the server. Or set TOWN_EXTRACT_ON_BOOT 1
# in HFWastelandZ_server.conf to write a side-by-side _generated.conf
# that doesn't clobber your edits.
# 
# CATEGORY GUESSING:
#  The extractor guesses the type from substrings in the name
#  (military / base / airport → military, industrial / factory → industrial,
#  bunker / vault → special, everything else → civilian). Override as needed.
# 
# RAW BASE TYPE INTEGER:
#  The 'engine_base_type' comment on each line is the raw integer from
#  MapItem.GetBaseType() (EMapDescriptorType). Useful for finer manual
#  filtering if you want to keep only certain map descriptor classes.
# 
# FORMAT (one town per line):
#   TOWN, Name, Radius, Type, X, Y, Z [, RadarOn, CircleVisible] [, veh:N]
# 
# REQUIRED FIELDS:
#   Name           - single token (spaces become underscores).
#                    Two entries with the same Name are de-duplicated:
#                    the second is skipped (TOWN_DEDUPE_MAP_NAMES=1, default).
#   Radius         - meters; in-world circle + loot zone size.
#   Type           - civilian | military | industrial | special
#                    Drives loot tier, vehicle slot tier, and circle color.
#   X, Y, Z        - world position of the town center.
# 
# OPTIONAL POSITIONAL FIELDS (in order, after Z):
#   RadarOn        - 0 = stealth town (no beacon ping when players enter)
#                    1 = normal radar warning  (default 1 if omitted)
#   CircleVisible  - 0 = hide the in-world boundary circle
#                    1 = render the colored circle  (default 1 if omitted)
# 
# OPTIONAL KEY:VALUE OVERRIDES (any position after Z):
#   veh:N          - override the vehicle slot count for THIS town only.
#                    Without it, count comes from the tier default in
#                    HFWastelandZ_server.conf (VEHICLES_PER_<TIER>).
#                    Example: veh:3 forces exactly 3 vehicle slots here.
# 
# DISABLING / COMMENTING OUT:
#   Lines beginning with #  or  // are skipped entirely. Use this to
#   disable a town without losing its data - re-enable later by deleting
#   the leading #. Trailing comments after a TOWN line are also tolerated.
# 
# EXAMPLES:
#   TOWN, Heather_Bay, 300, civilian, 605.7, -19.4, 3296.3
#   #TOWN, Angler_Bluff, 150, civilian, 1299.9, 19.2, 1923.9    # disabled
#   TOWN, Military_Camp, 300, military, 1388.6, 36.1, 2376.8, 1, 1, veh:3
#   TOWN, Ghost_Town, 300, civilian, 600, 0, 600, 0, 0          # stealth + hidden
# ============================================================

